The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 26: Dabur India has made its first overseas acquisition of Turkish personal care firm Hobi Kozmetik Group for $69 million. The company has posted a 20.7 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 107.39 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 88.95 crore a year ago. It has also announced the issue of bonus shares to its shareholders in the ratio of 1:1.                            
	 Mumbai, July 26: The government will divest its stakes in Coal India Ltd, Power Grid Corporation, Hindustan Copper, Steel Authority of India and Manganese Ore India by March, Sumit Bose, secretary in the department of divestment, said.                             
	 New Delhi, July 26: SAIL will invest Rs 100 crore to revive its Uttar Pradesh unit, formerly known as Malvika Steel. SAIL acquired the defunct Malvika Steel for Rs 209 crore last year and rechristened it as the Jagdishpur SAIL Unit.                            
	 New Delhi, July 26: Sterlite Industries today said it had obtained a stay against a Rs 324-crore tax notice served on it by the government for allegedly violating some tax norms.                            
	 Calcutta, July 26: Shree Ganesh Jewellery House Ltd is aiming to become a $1-billion company by March. The firm reported net sales of Rs 3,473.17 crore during 2009-10.
                                                                                                                          
